article.headline: Florida Gulf Coast 61, Kennesaw State 57
article.story: FORT MYERS, Fla. -- Kyle Marks scored 19 points as Florida Gulf Coast defeated Kennesaw State 61-57 on Monday night. Delvin Franklin and Reggie Chambers also scored 12 points apiece for the Eagles (11-18, 7-11 Atlantic Sun Conference), who snapped a three-game losing streak with the win. The game was tied at 54 after Marks made two free throws with 4:08 remaining in the second half. Two minutes later, Kennesaw State (7-18, 3-13) took a 57-56 lead with a layup from Zadrian Gibson. But Florida Gulf Coast ended the game with a 4-0 spurt, and the Owls were 0-for-4 in the final 2 minutes. Kelvin McConnell led the Owls with 18 points in 40 minutes of play. Florida Gulf Coast shot 51.2 percent from the field (22-for-43), and outrebounded Kennesaw State 32-27.
